Load Data¶

In [2]:
def load_data(input_dir:str ='../'):
    train_df = pd.read_csv('../input/train.csv.zip')
    test_df = pd.read_csv('../input/test.csv.zip')
    feature_df = pd.read_csv('../input/features.csv.zip')
    feature_df = feature_df.drop(['IsHoliday'], axis=1)
    store_df = pd.read_csv('../input/stores.csv')
    train_df = train_df.merge(feature_df, on=['Store', 'Date'], how='left')
    test_df = test_df.merge(feature_df, on=['Store', 'Date'], how='left')
    train_df = train_df.merge(store_df, on=['Store'], how='left')
    test_df = test_df.merge(store_df, on=['Store'], how='left')
    return train_df, test_df

訓練とテストの重複割合¶

In [10]:
def plot_venn2(df1:pd.DataFrame, df2:pd.DataFrame, col:str)-> None:
    n_intersect = len(set(df1[col]) & set(df2[col]))
    venn2((df1[col].nunique() - n_intersect, df2[col].nunique() - n_intersect, n_intersect))

# とりあえず11と12の祝日だけ切り出す関数は作っておく
def extract_holiday(df:pd.DataFrame, month:int):
    month2holiday = {
        11: "Thanksgiving",
        12: "Christmas"
    }
    holiday_name = month2holiday[month]
    df[holiday_name] = 0
    df.loc[df.query('IsHoliday==1 & month==@month').index, holiday_name] = 1
    return df
  • Sizeで売り上げをNormalize

import lightgbm as lgb
from sklearn.preprocessing import OrdinalEncoder
from sklearn.model_selection import GroupKFold
from tqdm import tqdm
  • 方針
    • validationの作成が相当難しい
    • test期間が9ヶ月なため、本来は9ヶ月未来をvalid、それ以前の期間の9ヶ月より後ろの期間で特徴量作成を行うべきであるが、それだと与えられてる期間から使える情報が少なくなってしまう。
    • そこで、上の時系列性から見てそこまで年ごとに変化がない、monthごとにGroupKFoldをしてsubmitしてみることで有効性を確かめる
    • 比較として単純に統計値を用いたものを提出する
      • Private: 3217.38001, Public: 3162.79282

def extract_date_feature(df:pd.DataFrame)-> pd.DataFrame:
    df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df["Date"], infer_datetime_format=True)
    df['month'] = df['Date'].dt.month
    df['day'] = df['Date'].dt.day
    # Normalize
    df['week'] = df['day'] // 7
    df.loc[df.query('week >= 4').index, 'week'] = 3
    df['weekofyear'] = df['Date'].dt.weekofyear
    return df

def extract_date_feature(df:pd.DataFrame)-> pd.DataFrame:
    df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df["Date"], infer_datetime_format=True)
    df['month'] = df['Date'].dt.month
    df['day'] = df['Date'].dt.day
    # Normalize
    df['week'] = df['day'] // 7
    df.loc[df.query('week >= 4 & month!=12').index, 'week'] = 3
    df['weekofyear'] = df['Date'].dt.weekofyear
    return df
